The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 11 September is 3,146 (364.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 07 September, there were 140 new confirmed cases (16.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 31 August, there were 47 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 198% (93 extra cases).
